  "prompt": "When will the Indian society actually become broad minded when it will come to religion?",
  "response": "Predicting when any society will become more broad-minded, especially regarding complex issues like religion, is challenging. Societal change tends to occur gradually and is influenced by numerous factors including education, socioeconomic development, exposure to diverse perspectives, and generational shifts in attitudes.\n\nIn India, there are ongoing efforts by various groups, civil society organizations, and individuals to promote secularism, tolerance, and interfaith harmony. Increased globalization, access to information, and dialogue might contribute to a more inclusive mindset over time. However, deep-rooted traditions and beliefs, political influences, and regional variations play significant roles in shaping collective attitudes.\n\nProgress can be observed in various aspects, such as legal reforms, the promotion of secular education, and open discussions on social media. Nonetheless, predicting an exact timeline is impossible. Continuous efforts toward awareness, communication, and education are essential for fostering a more open-minded society.",
